OL,6,FThe ASA continued: "The decision to
OL,7,Frevisit our original ruling took place
OL,8,Fin the context of the significant
OL,9,Fstrength of public feeling, including
OL,10,Fviews expressed by FKA twigs, in
OL,11,Fresponse to our findings, but was
OL,12,Fdriven by our concern that our
OL,13,Frationale for banning the ad was
OL,14,Fsubstantially flawed.
OL,16,F"We wanted to examine whether we had
OL,17,Fused inconsistent wording and if we
OL,18,Fhad made the right judgment about
OL,19,Fobjectification in the ad.
OL,21,F"Our republished ruling is final."
